# FailGuard Hybrid AI Failure Taxonomy
# Synthesized from David's two courses (May 2026)
# Version: 1.0

version: "1.0"
last_updated: "2026-05-05"
source: "David Macon's AI Failure Taxonomy courses + Microsoft Agentic Taxonomy + MIT Risk Repository"

categories:
  - name: Foundations
    description: Core definitions, history, and distinctions (failure vs limitation vs misuse)
    sub_modes:
      - name: What counts as an AI failure
        description: Any outcome that is harmful, incorrect, unjust, or misaligned with intent — even if the system behaved as designed
        enterprise_impact: "If you can't name it, you can't fix it or budget for it."
        legal_notes: "Establishes baseline for reasonable care and liability"

      - name: Failure vs limitation vs misuse
        description: Clear distinction between system faults, capability gaps, and human misapplication
        enterprise_impact: "Prevents wasting engineering time on the wrong problem"
        legal_notes: "Critical for distinguishing product liability from user error"

  - name: Data Failures
    description: Issues originating from training/evaluation data
    sub_modes:
      - name: Data quality and labeling errors
        enterprise_impact: "Ask where the training data came from and how it was labeled before you sign."
      - name: Distribution shift
        enterprise_impact: "A slow leak you may not notice until it's expensive."
      - name: Data poisoning and backdoor attacks
        enterprise_impact: "Know what to demand from vendors about data security and validation."
      - name: Representation and sampling bias
        enterprise_impact: "If your AI doesn't represent your customers, it will fail your customers."

  - name: Model Failures
    description: Issues in model training, architecture, or behavior
    sub_modes:
      - name: Overfitting, underfitting, and generalization failures
        enterprise_impact: "A model that only works in the lab is one you paid for but can't use."
      - name: Specification gaming and reward hacking
        enterprise_impact: "You told the AI to reduce ticket volume. It closed tickets without resolving them."
      - name: Hallucination and confabulation
        enterprise_impact: "Your AI cited a regulation that was repealed — confidently. That's a liability event."
      - name: Calibration failures
        enterprise_impact: "If 95% confident means wrong one in three times, someone is making decisions on a broken signal."

  - name: Systemic and Emergent Failures
    description: Failures that appear at scale or through interactions
    sub_modes:
      - name: Emergent and unpredictable behaviors
        enterprise_impact: "The AI worked fine in the pilot. Build that reality into deployment planning."
      - name: Multi-agent failure cascades
        enterprise_impact: "Do you know where your chain breaks?"
      - name: Goal misspecification and misalignment
        enterprise_impact: "Is your AI chasing your goals or just the proxy you gave it?"

  - name: Deployment and Societal Failures
    description: Failures caused by context, deployment, or societal impact
    sub_modes:
      - name: Failure modes in high-stakes domains
        enterprise_impact: "Regulators are already looking for this. Can you show you took the risks seriously?"
      - name: Feedback loops and model collapse
        enterprise_impact: "What is in your retraining data, and how much of it reflects the model's own past outputs?"
      - name: Security vulnerabilities and adversarial attacks
        enterprise_impact: "Your AI is a new attack surface. Have you included it in your threat model?"

  - name: Legal and Compliance
    description: Mapping failures to regulatory exposure
    sub_modes:
      - name: Colorado AI Act / California ADMT exposure
        enterprise_impact: "Up to $20k per violation + mandatory impact assessments and human review."
      - name: EU AI Act high-risk obligations
        enterprise_impact: "Conformity assessment deadline August 2026 — start now."
      - name: FTC Section 5 enforcement
        enterprise_impact: "AI washing and algorithmic harm are already enforceable."

# Fields available for every failure mode in FailGuard
fields:
  - name: enterprise_impact
  - name: legal_notes
  - name: mitigation_ideas
  - name: detection_signatures
  - name: multidimensional_dimensions
    description: "Links to latent space / trajectory mapping (future extension)"